# Current Goal

I want to expand this application to read all documents in the documents folder and create a catalogue of important elements of the world. The expected output is a new codex folder with a structure as follows:

- buildings
- characters
- events
- locations
- relics

The app should populate the folders with one file per entity it finds in the documents.

This should have two phases:

- First, get the LLM to compile a list of all of these things, and set up the folder structure.
- Then, populate the folders, one at a time.

## Structure

Each file should consist of the following:

- Title
- Description (~3 sentences, or ~6 sentences for important entries that occur often in the documents)
- History (~3 sentences, or ~6 sentences for important entries that occur often in the documents)
- Location (the name of a location in the locations folder, or, for a location, its region)
